<div class="container mt-5 main-content">
    <header>
        <h1>Health Tips for a Balanced Lifestyle</h1>
    </header>

    <main>
        <section>
            <h2>Nutrition & Diet:</h2>
            <p>Discover the power of nutritious foods! A balanced diet fuels your body, strengthens immunity, and boosts energy.</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Eat a balanced diet: Focus on fruits, vegetables, whole grains, lean protein, and healthy fats. </li>
                <li>Limit processed foods: Reduce your intake of sugary drinks, fast food, and heavily processed snacks. </li>
                <li>Choose high-fiber carbohydrates: Opt for whole grains and other fiber-rich foods. </li>
                <li>Stay hydrated: Drink plenty of water throughout the day. </li>
                <li>Consume less salt and sugar: Reduce your intake of these to improve overall health. </li>
                <li>Reduce intake of harmful fats: Limit saturated and trans fats. </li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Exercise & Fitness</h2>
            <p>Regular physical activity improves cardiovascular health, builds strength, and enhances mood.</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Get regular exercise: Aim for at least 30 minutes of moderate-intensity exercise most days of the week.</li>
                <li>Find activities you enjoy: Whether it's walking, running, swimming, or dancing, choose activities that you find fun and engaging.</li>
                <li>Get moving: Even small amounts of physical activity can make a difference. </li>
            </ul>
        </section>
        <section>
            <h2>Sleep:</h2>
            
            <ul>
                <li>Prioritize sleep: Aim for 7-9 hours of quality sleep per night</li>
                <li>Create a relaxing bedtime routine: Wind down before bed with a warm bath, reading, or meditation.</li>
                <li>Make sure your bedroom is dark, quiet, and cool: These factors can help improve sleep quality. </li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Mental Well-being & Stress Management</h2>
            <p>Prioritize mental health with mindfulness and relaxation techniques that bring balance to your day.</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Practice deep breathing and meditation</li>
                <li>Ensure you get quality sleep for optimal brain function</li>
                <li>Engage in hobbies and activities that bring joy</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Stress Management:</h2>
          <ul> 
            <li>Practice stress-reduction techniques: Meditation, yoga, deep breathing exercises, or spending time in nature can help reduce stress.</li>
            <li>Manage your time effectively: Prioritize tasks and avoid overcommitting yourself.</li>
            <li>Connect with loved ones: Spending time with friends and family can help reduce stress and improve your overall well-being. </li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Everyday Wellness Habits</h2>
            <p>Small daily habits contribute to long-term well-being and help you maintain a healthy lifestyle effortlessly.</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Stay hydrated and limit sugary drinks</li>
                <li>Maintain good posture to support joint health</li>
                <li>Develop consistent sleep patterns for better energy</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2> Other Important Tips:</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Have regular health check-ups: See your doctor for regular check-ups and screenings. </li>
                <li>Quit smoking: Smoking is one of the biggest preventable causes of death and disease. </li>
                <li>Limit alcohol consumption: If you choose to drink alcohol, do so in moderation. </li>
                <li>Practice good hygiene: Wash your hands frequently, especially before eating and after using the restroom. </li>
                <li>Be mindful of your mental health: Seek help if you are struggling with anxiety, depression, or other mental health issues. </li>
                <li>Follow traffic laws: This is a basic but important health tip to ensure your safety and the safety of others. </li>
                <li>Take antibiotics only as prescribed: This helps prevent antibiotic resistance. </li>
            </ul>
        </section>
    </main>
</div>
